                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure lies across SA. A cold front will clip the southeast on Tuesday morning, followed by a high pressure system which becomes dominant. The high is expected to move into the Tasman Sea by Friday as a cold front moves across the Bight.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
